  "prompt": "Who are Hindu Gods?",
  "response": "Hindu gods are deities worshipped in Hinduism, one of the world's oldest religions with origins tracing back over 4,000 years. Hinduism has a vast pantheon of gods and goddesses, each representing different aspects of life, nature, and the universe. Here are some of the major Hindu gods and goddesses:\n\n1. **Brahma**:\n   - Known as the creator god, Brahma is part of the Trimurti, the Hindu trinity that includes Vishnu and Shiva.\n   - He is often depicted with four heads, symbolizing the four Vedas, and four arms.\n\n2. **Vishnu**:\n   - Vishnu is the preserver of the universe and is also part of the Trimurti.\n   - He is known for his ten avatars (incarnations), including Rama and Krishna, who are revered deities in their own right.\n\n3. **Shiva**:\n   - Shiva is the destroyer and transformer within the Trimurti.\n   - He is often depicted in deep meditation or in the form of Nataraja, the cosmic dancer.\n\n4. **Ganesha**:\n   - The elephant-headed god, Ganesha, is the remover of obstacles and the patron of arts and sciences.\n   - He is one of the most widely worshipped deities in Hinduism.\n\n5. **Krishna**:\n   - An avatar of Vishnu, Krishna is a central figure in the Mahabharata and the Bhagavad Gita.\n   - He is revered for his teachings on dharma (duty/righteousness) and bhakti (devotion).\n\n6. **Rama**:\n   - Another avatar of Vishnu, Rama is the protagonist of the Ramayana.\n   - He is celebrated for his adherence to dharma and his victory over the demon king Ravana.\n\n7. **Durga**:\n   - Durga is a warrior goddess, often depicted riding a tiger or lion.\n   - She is revered as the destroyer of evil forces and is especially worshipped during the festival of Durga Puja.\n\n8. **Lakshmi**:\n   - The goddess of wealth, prosperity, and good fortune, Lakshmi is the consort of Vishnu.\n   - She is often depicted with four arms, holding symbols of prosperity and purity.\n\n9. **Saraswati**:\n   - The goddess of knowledge, music, art, and wisdom, Saraswati is often depicted with a veena (a musical instrument) and a book.\n   - She is worshipped by students and scholars.\n\n10. **Hanuman**:\n    - A devoted follower of Rama, Hanuman is known for his strength, courage, and loyalty.\n    - He is often worshipped for protection and overcoming obstacles.\n\nThese deities are just a few examples from a diverse and extensive pantheon, and their worship varies across different regions and traditions within Hinduism. Each god and goddess has numerous stories, festivals, and rituals associated with them, reflecting the rich tapestry of Hindu mythology and culture.",
